```
$ man podman-secret-create

   --label, -l=key=val1,key2=val2
       Add label to secret. These labels can be viewed in podman secrete inspect or ls.
```
```
$ podman secret create --label=key1=val1,key2=val2,scopes=dns tokens tokens.ini
abcdefabcdefabcdefabcdef0
```
```
$ podman secret inspect tokens
[
    {
        "ID": "abcdefabcdefabcdefabcdef0",
        "CreatedAt": "<some-timestamp>",
        "UpdatedAt": "<some-timestamp>",
        "Spec": {
            "Name": "tokens",
            "Driver": {
                "Name": "file",
                "Options": {
                    "path": "/var/lib/containers/storage/secrets/filedriver"
                }
            },
            "Labels": {
                "key1": "val1,key2=val2,scopes=dns"
            }
        }
    }
]
```

Apparently, according to tests, a colon `:` can be used as key/value separator, but it's not mentioned anywhere? Never mind, it's not a replacement for the equal sign `=`, a label without an `=` character would be all key no value. It doesn't help much that the test case is just like `stdout.contains()`.
